This suite tests for namespace pollution in the standard headers.

The system headers are preprocessed and compared with the API definition files
from the include suite, which states what declarations are allowed per each
POSIX option. Each header is compiled twice, first with `_POSIX_C_SOURCE`, and
secondly with `_XOPEN_SOURCE`, and each declaration is verified. The header test
will fail if any declaration exists that is not part of the POSIX API, or if the
declaration has the wrong type, unless the declaration is inside the header's
reserved namespace.

Click the pollution link for any failing headers to see what declarations were
rejected.
